Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens; finely chop half the greens. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%unit}. Halve @Super Select cucumber{1}(halved crosswise, save one half for another use). Quarter cucumber lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Dice @tomato{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped).

> For 4 servings, use whole cucumber instead of halving.

== Lemon Scallion Yogurt Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @yogurt{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, chopped scallion greens, a squeeze of lemon juice from half the lemon, and a pinch of lemon zest. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Chickpea Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, combine chickpeas, cucumber, tomato, scallion whites, sliced scallion greens, parsley, juice from half the lemon, remaining lemon zest, 1 tsp @Za'atar spice{1%tablespoon}(divided) (you'll use the rest in the next step), and 2 TBSP @olive oil{2%tablespoon}. Season generously with salt and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use juice of a whole lemon, 2 tsp Za'atar Spice, and 4 TBSP olive oil.

== Barramundi ==

Pat @barramundi{10%ounce}(pat dry with paper towels) dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with remaining Za'atar spice, salt, and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large, preferably nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add barramundi and cook until opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Remove from heat.

== To Serve ==

Divide barramundi and chickpea salad between #plates{}. Squeeze as much remaining lemon juice over barramundi as you like. Drizzle everything with yogurt sauce and serve.